-	Nested parallel effects were not dealing with targets in children. (CompositeEffect)
-	Composite effects were capturing values for child effects property (need to have child effects only capture values for their targets, not any other targets in the overall effect) (CompositeEffect)

-	3D Transform effects were not correctly dealing with transform centers that were staying in place during the effect. We needed to force the postTranslationX/Y properties to be animated, even though they might be unchanging. (AnimateTransform)

-	Supplying Fade in a trigger for a popupAnchor caused an RTE due to a bad assumption about components vs groups. This fix doesn’t actually made fading work (new effects don’t deal with triggers), but it prevents the crash (EffectManager)
Tests run: checkintests, Mustella spark/effects, mx/effects
